    <bioghist>Resident of Oakfield Township, Kent County, Mich., who served in Co. C, 13th Michigan Infantry, during the Civil War.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Chiefly letters to Tower from his father Samuel Tower and other relatives, describing life in Kent County during the war; also letters written by other members of the 13th Michigan Infantry to Tower after he was wounded in 1863 and separated from his unit; describing their activities in Georgia; and letters from Tower's cousin Eustace Tower, a soldier in the 13th Battery of Michigan Artillery, describing garrison duty near Washington, D.C., and the search for the assassins of Abraham Lincoln.</scopecontent>
